tourBios.curYrHigh: Earned PGA TOUR Latinoamérica status for the second consecutive year with a T11 finish at the Mazatlán, Mexico Q-School in January. Won a four-man playoff for one spot that secured exempt status for the first half of the season.
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica as runner-up at the Buenos Aires, Argentina Q-School in January… Had one top-25 and nine cuts made in 12 starts to finish the year ranked 89th on the Order of Merit… His best finish was T16 at the Aberto do Brasil in Rio de Janeiro in September.

2014: Monday qualified for the Wyndham Championship to make his first career start on the PGA TOUR. Shot 72-68 to miss the cut by two shots at Sedgefield CC in Greensboro, NC.

2013: Won his hometown's Salisbury Classic on the eGolf Tour. Carded a final round 64 to enter a sudden death playoff, where he emerged victorious over Dustin Bray on the third extra hole… Had runner-up finishes at the River Landing Open and Northstone Open, also on the eGolf Tour.

2012: Made the cut and finished T57 at the Stadion Classic at UGA in Athens, GA on his first career start on the Web.com Tour… Played on the eGolf Tour, where his best finish was third at the Oldfield Open in Hilton Head Island, SC.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf at the University of Virginia, where he was team captain on his senior year… Had one college win at the 2011 Kenridge Invitational… Named ACC All-Academic in 2010 and 2011… Recipient of Weaver-James-Corrigan Scholarship… Posted a score of 60 in a qualifier for the 2011 U.S. Amateur Championship.
tourBios.personal: Has a sister, Casey… Graduated from the University of Virginia in 2011 with a degree in kinesiology… Hobbies include fly-fishing and duck hunting… Kelley Phillips and Patrick Kelly (current) are the golf instructor he has worked with… Says his biggest thrill in golf is hooking big fish… Pine Valley has been his favorite golf course to play… Ernie Els is his favorite athlete to watch… His dad, his grandfather and U.S. President Ronald Reagan would round out his dreamed foursome… Wants to go fly-fishing all over the world… Personal motto: “To give anything less than your best, is to sacrifice the gift”… Twitter name is WCollins_Golf… Instagram name is @wc4_hoos
tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 2-11 at 2016 Q-School (exempt to midseason reshuffle)
